-- Helicopter Crashes in Waters Off Hong Kong; 13 Aboard Rescued, RTHK Says
-- Hanny Wan
-- 2010-07-03T05:24:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-03/helicopter-crashes-in-waters-off-hong-kong-13-aboard-rescued-rthk-says.html

          
          
             A helicopter carrying 11 passengers
and two crew crashed into the waters around Hong Kong island,
Radio Television Hong Kong reported.  
 All 13 aboard the aircraft were rescued, RTHK reported on
its website. One male passenger was admitted to Queen Mary
Hospital, it said.  
 The helicopter, operated by  Sky Shuttle Helicopters Ltd. ,
went down about 100 meters offshore from  Shun Tak Centre  in
Hong Kongâ€™s Sheung Wan district, according to RTHK.  
 Sky Shuttle is the sole commercial helicopter operator
between Hong Kong, Macau and Shenzhen, according to its website.  
